370        @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
371        protected <T extends ModelElement> T findByURI(Class<T> type, URI uri) {
372                Resource res = eResource(); 
373                if (res != null) {
374                        ResourceSet rSet = res.getResourceSet();
375                        TreeIterator<?> cit = rSet == null ? res.getAllContents() : rSet. getAllContents();
376                        while (cit.hasNext()) {
377                                Object next = cit.next(); 
378                                if (type.isInstance(next)) {
379                                        for (URI nextURI: NcoreUtil.getIdentifiers((T) next)) {
380                                                if (nextURI != null && nextURI.equals(uri)) {                                   
381                                                        return (T) next;
382                                                }
383                                        }
384                                }
385                        }
386                }               
387                List<? extends org.nasdanika.persistence.Marker> pMarkers = new ArrayList<>();
388                List<? extends Marker> mMarkers = getMarkers();
389                if (mMarkers == null || mMarkers.isEmpty()) {
390                        org.nasdanika.persistence.Marked pMarked = (org.nasdanika.persistence.Marked) EcoreUtil.getRegisteredAdapter(this, type);
391                        if (pMarked != null) {
392                                pMarkers = pMarked.getMarkers();
393                        }
394                } else {
395                        pMarkers = mMarkers.stream().map(mMarker -> new org.nasdanika.persistence.MarkerImpl(mMarker.getLocation(), mMarker.getPosition())).collect(Collectors.toList());
396                }               
397                throw new ConfigurationException("Could not find " + type.getName() + " with uri " + uri, pMarkers);
398        }

421        /**
422         * Resolves proxy URI against this element URI - this allows to have both logical and physical proxies.
423         * a logical proxy URI shall be prefixed with ./ and can be relative.
424         */
425        @Override
426        public URI eProxyURI() {
427                URI eProxyURI = super.eProxyURI();
428                if (eProxyURI != null && eProxyURI.isRelative()) {
429                        for (URI base: NcoreUtil.getIdentifiers(this)) {
430                                if (base != null && !base.isRelative() && base.isHierarchical()) {
431                                        return eProxyURI.resolve(base);
432                                }
433                        }
434                }
435                return eProxyURI;
436        }

466        /**
467         * If argument is a proxy - resolves it. If it is not resolved throws {@link ConfigurationException} with a {@link org.nasdanika.common.persistence.Marker} from the proxy if it is {@link org.nasdanika.common.persistence.Marked} 
468         * and has a marker or from this object.  
469         * @param <E>
470         * @param eObject
471         * @return
472         */
473        @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
474        protected <E extends EObject> E resolveProxy(E eObject) {
475                if (eObject.eIsProxy()) {
476                        eObject = (E) EcoreUtil.resolve(eObject, this);
477                        if (eObject.eIsProxy()) { // Not resolved.
478                                List<? extends org.nasdanika.persistence.Marker> markers = null;
479                                if (eObject instanceof org.nasdanika.persistence.Marked) {
480                                        markers = ((org.nasdanika.persistence.Marked) eObject).getMarkers();
481                                }
482                                throw new ConfigurationException("Unresolved proxy: " + eObject, markers == null || markers.isEmpty() ? getMarkers() : markers);
483                        }
484                }
485                return eObject; 
486        }
